where 〈D50〉 and 〈h〉 are channel-averaged median grain size and bankfull depth, respectively). Although the Claret Conglomerate appears to meet the specific criteria outlined by Paola and Mohrig24, the Esplugafreda channels encased in cohesive floodplain banks and interpreted as sinuous ribbons4 likely do not. Thus, we employ a more generalized empirical relationship for alluvial rivers developed by Trampush25:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
